Communicated by:
ProMED

[According to the European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control, "Since the beginning of the 2022 transmission season and as of 28 Sep 2022, EU/EEA countries have reported 851 human cases of WNV infection in Italy (536), Greece (231), Romania (43), Hungary (14), Germany (8), Croatia (8), Austria (6), Spain (4), and Slovakia (1). EU/EEA countries have reported 53 deaths in Italy (28), Greece (20), and Romania (5). EU-neighboring countries have reported 187 human cases of WNV infection in Serbia (187) and 8 deaths in Serbia (8).

"Since the beginning of the 2022 transmission season, 62 outbreaks among equids and 238 outbreaks among birds have been reported by EU/EEA countries. Outbreaks among equids have been reported by Italy (36), Germany (9), Greece (4), Spain (4), Croatia (4), France (2), Hungary (2), and Austria (1). Outbreaks among birds have been reported by Italy (191), Germany (41), Spain (4), Austria (1), and Hungary (1)."
(https://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/west-nile-fever/surveillance-and-disease-data/disease-data-ecdc; updated 28 Sep 2022).
